On Sun, Sep 26, 1999 at 01:56:46PM -0500, Oliver Xymoron wrote:
> > Unfortunately, code is also a poor substitute for documentation.
> 
> In some real sense, the code is perfect documentation. It _is_ complete,
> accurate, and uptodate. The problem we have is that it's sometimes not
> lucid. 
Code can only document what you're actually doing, not what you're
supposed to be doing.  In other words it can only document practice,
not policy.
